Drumstick is one of my all time favourites, we make sihi bendi a dish to have with curd rice, amongst many others. The drumstick pod is a powerful aphrodisiac, and contains significant amount of vitamin c. The leaves are rich in Quercetin which helps lower blood pressure. 

A decoction of leaf powder and water is useful for eczema, hypertension, sexual debility and also helps in painful periods and hormonal acne. It is also wonderful for diabetics since the chologenic acid helps in lowering blood sugar levels and improving insulin sensitivity. A lot of my hypothyroid clients have benefited from taking moringa water, and I find that the metabolism improves greatly when it is added to a balanced diet. 

The flower is made into chutney or palya and aids healthy breast milk production. Moringa should be part of the diet during pregnancy and after childbirth since it is rich in many micronutrients which become depleted in the time. 

It is a part of many Ayurvedic medicines including Murivenna one of the most powerful healing oils for external injuries.

Using a herb in cooking is the best, next best is pure powder. I do not recommend capsules since the absorption of any medicine starts in the mouth and happens through the gut, and the taste stimulates certain reflex hormones, which we miss when we take capsules. 
